This paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The problem studied in the paper, unrelated machine scheduling, involves allocating resources to tasks, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-off between efficiency metrics, which is a topic in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes optimal mechanisms, which is a topic in economics and decision theory (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to derive bounds and characterize the Pareto frontier, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
